The African National Congress (ANC) in Limpopo says all logistical arrangements are in place to host the party’s annual January 8 statement and 110th anniversary in Polokwane. About two thousand party members will be allowed to attend the celebrations at the Peter Mokaba stadium. Some of the ruling party leaders are expected to start arriving from tomorrow. The rally will be addressed by ANC President Cyril Ramaphosa. The party’s provincial spokesperson Donald Selamolela says they are ready to host the event. “You can see we are in the stadium trying to tight loose ends. The security details are here everyone is here. We preparing of course the birthday of the glorious movement, the biggest liberation movement on the African continent. We are very very happy the national leadership will be arriving at various deployments with effect from tomorrow, inter-phasing with our members, engaging with communities.” ANC President Cyril Ramaphosa to lead the event at the Old Peter Mokaba Stadium: 